TY  - JOUR
AU  - Feunou, Bruno
AU  - Jahan-Parvar, Mohammad R.
AU  - Tédongap, Roméo
T1  - Modeling Market Downside Volatility*
PY  - 2013
Y1  - 2013/01/01
DO  - 10.1093/rof/rfr024
JO  - Review of Finance
JA  - Rev Financ
VL  - 17
IS  - 1
SP  - 443
EP  - 481
SN  - 1572-3097
AB  - We propose a new methodology for modeling and estimating time-varying downside
                    risk and upside uncertainty in equity returns and for assessment of risk–return
                    trade-off in financial markets. Using the salient features of the binormal
                    distribution, we explicitly relate downside risk and upside uncertainty to
                    conditional heteroskedasticity and asymmetry through binormal GARCH (BiN-GARCH)
                    model. Based on S&amp;P 500 and international index returns, we find strong
                    empirical support for existence of significant relative downside risk, and
                    robust positive relationship between relative downside risk and conditional
                    mode.
Y2  - 3/26/2024
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1093/rof/rfr024
ER  - 



