TY  - JOUR
AU  - Claessens, Stijn
AU  - Yafeh, Yishay
T1  - Comovement of Newly Added Stocks with National Market Indices: Evidence from Around the World*
PY  - 2013
Y1  - 2013/01/01
DO  - 10.1093/rof/rfs001
JO  - Review of Finance
JA  - Rev Financ
VL  - 17
IS  - 1
SP  - 203
EP  - 227
SN  - 1572-3097
AB  - We document increased stock price comovement for companies added to major indices around the world. Using data on forty developed and emerging markets for 10 years, we find that in most markets, when added to a major index, firms experience an increase in their beta (especially if their pre-inclusion beta is low) and in the extent to which market returns explain firm stock returns (R2). Stock turnover and analyst coverage also typically increase upon inclusion. Various empirical tests suggest that the category/habitat views of Barberis, Shleifer and Wurgler explain most of these results, although information-related factors also account for some findings.
Y2  - 3/26/2024
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1093/rof/rfs001
ER  - 



